{"lemma":"سَبِطَةٍ","slug":"سَبِطَةٍ","root":"س.ب.ط","root_slug":"س-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ط","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":15},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18722","n18725","n18726","n18727","n18728","n18729"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be lanky"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be well-shaped, to be graceful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be liberal, to be bountiful, to be munificent, to be generous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to miscarry"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lanky"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-shaped, graceful"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"liberal, bountiful, munificent, generous"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"buffelgrasses (Cenchrus gen. et spp.)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Stipagrostis spp.","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandchild from the mother's side"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grandchild"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribe of the Israelites"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet)","examples":[{"text":"أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ أُعْطِينَا سِتًّا وَفُضِّلْنَا بِسَبْعٍ أُعْطِينَا الْعِلْمَ وَالْحِلْمَ وَالسَّمَاحَةَ وَالْفَصَاحَةَ وَالشَّجَاعَةَ وَالْمَحَبَّةَ فِي قُلُوبِ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ وَفُضِّلْنَا بِأَنَّ مِنَّا النَّبِيَّ الْمُخْتَارَ مُحَمَّدًا وَمِنَّا الصِّدِيقَ وَمِنَّا الطَّيَارَ وَمِنَّا أَسَدَ اللهِ وَأَسَدَ رَسُولِهِ وَمِنَّا سِبْطَا هٰذِهِ الْأُمَّةِ مَنْ عَرَفَنِي فَقَدْ عَرَفَنِي وَمَنْ لَمْ يَعْرِفْنِي أَنْبَأْتُهُ بِحَسَبِيّ وَنَسَبِيّ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet); al-Ḥusayn ibn ʿAlī or al-Ḥasan ibn ʿAlī","tags":["definite","especially"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wand, staff","tags":["rare"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *šabṭ- (literally “staff, rod”). Semantically influenced by Hebrew שֵׁבֶט (śeḇeṭ, “tribe of Israel; staff, sceptre”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18722","headword_ar":"سَبِطَ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, S, M, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuTa","text_ar":"سَبُطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTN","text_ar":"سَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the former verb, (S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the K, as is remarked in the TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwTapN","text_ar":"سُبُوطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) which is of the latter verb, (M, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaATapN","text_ar":"سَبَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwTN","text_ar":"سُبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which are also of the latter verb; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(hair, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lank, not crisp:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * Msb, K: *) or the former verb is used in this sense, said of hair; and the latter is said of a man, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lank, not crisp, in his hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaATapN","text_ar":"سَبَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", relating to a man, also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being long in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alowaAH","text_ar":"اَلْوَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawoHN","text_ar":"لَوْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and even therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuTa","text_ar":"سَبُطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaATapN","text_ar":"سَبَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTa","text_ar":"سَبِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTN","text_ar":"سَبَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"facile,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِالْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwTapN","text_ar":"سُبُوطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is likewise expl. as signifying (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being liberal, bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaATapN","text_ar":"سَبَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", relating to rain, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being abundant and extensive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K, TA.) [―         -b5-  See also the part. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTa Ealayohi AlEaTaA='a","text_ar":"سَبَطَ عَلَيْهِ العَطَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave to him successive and large gifts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subiTa","text_ar":"سُبِطَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was affected with fever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaATi","text_ar":"سَبَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n18725","headword_ar":"سَبْطٌ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18726","headword_ar":"سِبْطٌ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grandchild;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a son's child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a daughter's child:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, TA;) which is commonly used by the vulgar as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daughters' children;"},{"kind":"text","text":"distinguished by them from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHofaAdN","text_ar":"اَحْفَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which they apply to son's children, pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafiydN","text_ar":"حَفِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but the leading lexicologists expressly declare that it includes sons' children and daughters' children, as it is said to do by ISd: IAar explained"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTN","text_ar":"سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTaAni","text_ar":"سِبْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particularly distinguished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choicest, of children."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasanu waAlHusayonu siboTaA rasuwli A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"الحَسَنُ وَالحُسَيْنُ سِبْطَا رَسُولِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Hasan, and El-Hoseyn are the two grandsons of the Apostle of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA. *) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe of the Jews:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTN","text_ar":"سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) in relation to the Jews, (M, Msb,) or [rather] the Children of Israel, (S,) being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylapN","text_ar":"قَبِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaAy^ilu","text_ar":"قَبَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) in relation to the Arabs: (S, M, Msb:) and the former are thus called to distinguish them from the children of Ishmael. (M, TA.) In the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaT~aEonaAhumu A@vonataYo","text_ar":"وَقَطَّعْنَاهُمُ ا@ثْنَتَىْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orapa A^asobaATFA","text_ar":"عَشْرَةَ اَسْبَاطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we divided them into twelve"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1295},{"kind":"text","text":"divisions,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribes"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, M, K,) in the Kur [vii. 160], (S, M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsbATA","text_ar":"اسباطا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute (S, M, K) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AvntY","text_ar":"اثنتى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$rp","text_ar":"عشرة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) not a specificative, (S, M, K,) because the specificative may only be a sing.; (S, M;) the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqT~EnAhm AvntY E$rp firoqapF","text_ar":"وقطّعناهم اثنتى عشرة فِرْقَةً"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsbATFA","text_ar":"اسباطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, Zj, S,) and therefore the numeral is fem.; (Akh, S;) or this is a mistake; for it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaqFA AvntY E$rp","text_ar":"فِرَقًا اثنتى عشرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore the numeral is fem. (Abu-l-'Abbás, TA.) Accord. to Ktr, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA siboTN","text_ar":"هٰذَا سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi siboTN","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i siboTN","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and using"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbT","text_ar":"سبط"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firoqapN","text_ar":"فِرْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The saying"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaA^an~ahu siboTN mina AlA^asobaATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [asserted to be] a mistake, inasmuch as its author imagined that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTN","text_ar":"سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) IDrd ascribes it to El-'Ajjáj or Ru-beh: it occurs in an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urojuwzap","text_ar":"اُرْجُوزَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the latter. (Sgh, TA.) [But it is applied to a single man: for] it is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusayonN siboTN mina AlA^asobaATi","text_ar":"حُسَيْنٌ سِبْطٌ مِنَ الاَسْبَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoseyn is"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though he were]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a nation of the nations"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~apN mina","text_ar":"اُمَّةٌ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^umami","text_ar":"الاُمَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in goodness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so expl. by Aboo-Bekr: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the fathers of tribes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the multitude of his descendants: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the sons of daughters."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So in a marginal note in a copy of the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer ” of Es-Suyootee.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A generation"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaron","text_ar":"قَرْن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes after another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTN riboEiy~apN","text_ar":"سِبْطٌ رِبْعِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in the present art. and in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbE","text_ar":"ربع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboEiy~apN","text_ar":"رِبْعِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTN","text_ar":"سَبَطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so accord. to a copy of the M, in the present art.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A palmtree of which the fruit ripens in the end of the summer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot-season."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","Msb","K","S","Akh","Zj"]},{"entry_id":"n18727","headword_ar":"سَبَطٌ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, first sentence.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as is fresh of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliY~","text_ar":"حَلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the plants of the sands;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) [i. e.] the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSiY~","text_ar":"نَصِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"while fresh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it has dried up, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliY~","text_ar":"حَلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A'Obeyd, S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyl","text_ar":"ثِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except that it becomes tall; growing in the sands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, S:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of those that, when they dry up, become white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as is said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliY~","text_ar":"حَلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling hoariness, like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vumaAm","text_ar":"ثُمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panic grass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AHn, O: in the TA, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nam~aAm","text_ar":"نَمَّام"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is asserted that the Arabs say, “ The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAn","text_ar":"صِلِّيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the bread of the camels, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaT","text_ar":"سَبَط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyS","text_ar":"خَبِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” (AHn, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its manner of growth is like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxon","text_ar":"دُخْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is a good pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) AHn says, a desert-Arab, of 'Anazeh, told me that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its manner of growth is like that of large"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxon","text_ar":"دُخْن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling short of"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna","text_ar":"دُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urap","text_ar":"ذُرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it has grain like the grain termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bazor","text_ar":"بَزْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which will not come forth from its envelopes but by bruising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pounding, and men extract it and eat it, made into bread, and cooked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O:) the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree that has many branches and one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stem"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) so says Az.; adding that hence is derived"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaATN","text_ar":"اَسْبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siboTN","text_ar":"سِبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though the father represented the tree and the children represented the branches: (TA: [but this is questionable:]) accord. to Abo-Ziyád,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing in the sands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall, having slender branches, eaten by the camels and the sheep or goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and collected by men, who sell it upon the roads"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlT~uruqi","text_ar":"عَلَى الطُّرُقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (AHn, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the tamarisk"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa AlT~arofaA='i","text_ar":"مَعَ الطَّرْفَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (so in the TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without blossom and without thorns, having thin leaves of the size of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kur~aAv","text_ar":"كُرَّاث"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leek"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (AHn, M, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when this first comes forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O.) ―         -b2-  See also the last sentence of the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":["Lth","TA","S","AHn","O","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n18728","headword_ar":"سَبِطٌ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaTN","text_ar":"سَبَطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (the first and third of these in one copy of the S, and the second alone in another copy of the S, and all in the M and Msb and K,) the first of the dial. of El- Hijáz, (TA,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTa","text_ar":"سَبِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the second from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuTa","text_ar":"سَبُطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the last being an inf. n. used as an epithet, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lank, not crisp;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * Msb, K; *) applied to hair: (S, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaATN","text_ar":"سِبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said by Sb to be of the measure most common for a pl. of an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Al$~aEari","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الشَّعَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having lank hair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaATN","text_ar":"سِبَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone, applied to a number of persons. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also metonymically applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A foreigner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as [its contr.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEodN","text_ar":"جَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is to an Arab. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) applied to a man: (M:) or, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Aljisomi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alowaAH","text_ar":"اَلْوَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawoH","text_ar":"لَوْح"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, TA,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and even therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Aljisomi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to different copies of the K,) or both, (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly in stature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proportion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and evenness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having extended limbs, and perfect in make."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu AlqaSabi","text_ar":"سَبِطُ القَصَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhaA","text_ar":"سَبْطُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", A man ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long and even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, and without protuberances, in the bones of the fore arms and the shanks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu AlbanaAni","text_ar":"سَبِطُ البَنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTuhaA","text_ar":"سَبْطُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long in the fingers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu","text_ar":"سَبِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqi","text_ar":"الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank in make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rd","text_ar":"رد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTapu Alxaloqi","text_ar":"سَبِطَةُ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTatuhu","text_ar":"سَبْطَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  a woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender, in make."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Z, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu","text_ar":"سَبِطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAqayoni","text_ar":"السَّاقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flaccid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncompact, in the shanks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 238.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyadayoni","text_ar":"اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTu","text_ar":"سَبْطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTuhumaA","text_ar":"سَبِطُهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, and so in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTu Alkaf~ayoni","text_ar":"سَبِطُ الكَفَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)  A man who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal, bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiTN","text_ar":"سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlomaEoruwfi","text_ar":"بِالْمَعْرُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"facile, in beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarN sabiTN","text_ar":"مَطَرٌ سَبِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboTN","text_ar":"سَبْطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain pouring abundantly and extensively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and consecutively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","S","M","K","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n18729","headword_ar":"سِبِطٌّ","root":"sbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibit~N","text_ar":"سِبِتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}